record_data.record_plain_text: GATEWAY ENERGY MARKETING MARKET-BASED RATE TARIFF 1. Availability: Gateway Energy Marketing (Gateway) makes wholesale electric energy and capacity available under this Rate Schedule to any purchaser with whom it has entered into a tariff. 2. Applicability: This schedule is applicable to all sales of energy or capacity by Gateway not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of Gateway. 3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Gateway. 4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Gateway. 5. Affiliate Sales Prohibited: No sale may be made pursuant to this Rate Schedule to an entity owned or controlled by, or under common control with, Gateway or to any entity affiliated with the public utility selling any portion of the energy or capacity to Gateway which is being offered for resale under this Rate Schedule. 6. Effective Date: This Rate Schedule is effective on the date set by the Commission. 7. Change In Status: Gateway must timely report to the Commission any change in status that would reflect a departure from the characteristics the Commission relied upon in granting market-based rate authority. A change in status includes, but is not limited to, each of the following: (i) ownership or control of generation or transmission facilities or inputs to electric power production other than fuel supplies, or (ii) affiliation with any entity not disclosed in the application for market-based rate authority that owns or controls generation or transmission facilities or inputs to electric power production, or affiliation with any entity that has a franchised service area. Any change in status must be filed no later than 30 days after the change in status occurs.
